[cid:image002.png@01D15391.AC39AF80]

Dear Colleague,

we are pleased to invite you to attend the iTi Conference on Turbulence VII=
 in Bertinoro, Italy, September 7-9, 2016. The iTi (interdisciplinary Turbu=
lence initiative) is a series of conferences organized in order to focus on=
 different aspects of both fundamental and applied turbulence research. The=
refore, both engineers and physicists working in the field of turbulence ar=
e invited to join it.

Topics comprise themes such as: Fundamentals, Modelling, Simulation (DNS an=
d LES), Mathematical Methods, Coherent structure/Vortices, Scaling Laws and=
 Intermittency, Large Re flows experiments, Convection, Polymer and Scalar,=
 Scalar Mixing and Particle, Turbulent Boundary Layers, Atmospheric flows a=
nd MHD.

The seventh conference of the iTi series will again take place in one of th=
e most beautiful conference centers in Europe: the University Centre of Ber=
tinoro. The Centre is located in three large historical and monumental buil=
dings on the top of an ancient town. For further details please check here =
http://www.ceub.it/default.asp?id=3D346#.UqmvjHxQA_Q.

Like in the previous editions the peer reviewed proceedings will be publish=
ed in the volume "Progress in Turbulence VII" by Springer.

The iTi conference will be this year combined with a two-day workshop on Hi=
gh Reynolds number Wall Bounded Turbulent Flows, September 5-6, 2016, organ=
ised by the European consortium EuHIT  (European High-Performance Infrastru=
ctures in Turbulence). The aim of the workshop is to present the new operat=
ive facility "Long Pipe" in CICLoPE (University of Bologna) to both Industr=
ial and Scientific community and to discuss recent developments in measurem=
ent and processing techniques. To attend this workshop an additional regist=
ration is required.

List of iTi invited key-note speakers:
Prof. Alexander Smits, Princeton University
Prof. Bruno Eckhard, University of Marburg
Prof. Paolo Orlandi, Universit=E0 di Roma La Sapienza
Prof. Philipp Schlatter, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm
Prof. Michael Wilczek, Max Planck Institute for Dynamics, G=F6ttingen

Dates and deadlines:
Abstract submission: April 19th, 2016
Response/accepting the contribution: June 30th, 2014
Early registration for Conference and Workshop: until July 15th, 2016
Late registration for Conference and Workshop: until September 1st, 2016
Submission of full paper: October 28th, 2016

All the essential information is already available on the conference Websit=
e http://www.fdy.tu-darmstadt.de/iti2016/iti2014_1/Home.en.jsp where also L=
aTeX and Word templates for the preparation of the abstracts are made avail=
able.

We are very happy to welcome you in Bertinoro.

We are looking forward to hearing from you soon

Best wishes

________________________________
Martin Oberlack (Technische Universit=E4t Darmstadt)
Joachim Peinke (Universit=E4t Oldenburg / ForWind)
Alessandro Talamelli (Universit=E0 di Bologna)

PS: Please note that September 13-16, 2016 there will be EFMC in Sevilla/Sp=
ain.



--_000_285DB6A636DB57429E9BFC250518D70003980797EX102adstudarms_

[cid:image002.png@01D15391.AC39AF80]

Dear Colleague,

we are pleased to invite you to attend the iTi Conference on Turbulence VII=
 in Bertinoro, Italy, September 7-9, 2016. The iTi (interdisciplinary Turbu=
lence initiative) is a series of conferences organized in order to focus on=
 different aspects of both fundamental and applied turbulence research. The=
refore, both engineers and physicists working in the field of turbulence ar=
e invited to join it.

Topics comprise themes such as: Fundamentals, Modelling, Simulation (DNS an=
d LES), Mathematical Methods, Coherent structure/Vortices, Scaling Laws and=
 Intermittency, Large Re flows experiments, Convection, Polymer and Scalar,=
 Scalar Mixing and Particle, Turbulent Boundary Layers, Atmospheric flows a=
nd MHD.

The seventh conference of the iTi series will again take place in one of th=
e most beautiful conference centers in Europe: the University Centre of Ber=
tinoro. The Centre is located in three large historical and monumental buil=
dings on the top of an ancient town. For further details please check here =
http://www.ceub.it/default.asp?id=3D346#.UqmvjHxQA_Q.

Like in the previous editions the peer reviewed proceedings will be publish=
ed in the volume "Progress in Turbulence VII" by Springer.

The iTi conference will be this year combined with a two-day workshop on Hi=
gh Reynolds number Wall Bounded Turbulent Flows, September 5-6, 2016, organ=
ised by the European consortium EuHIT  (European High-Performance Infrastru=
ctures in Turbulence). The aim of the workshop is to present the new operat=
ive facility "Long Pipe" in CICLoPE (University of Bologna) to both Industr=
ial and Scientific community and to discuss recent developments in measurem=
ent and processing techniques. To attend this workshop an additional regist=
ration is required.

List of iTi invited key-note speakers:
Prof. Alexander Smits, Princeton University
Prof. Bruno Eckhard, University of Marburg
Prof. Paolo Orlandi, Universit=E0 di Roma La Sapienza
Prof. Philipp Schlatter, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm
Prof. Michael Wilczek, Max Planck Institute for Dynamics, G=F6ttingen

Dates and deadlines:
Abstract submission: April 19th, 2016
Response/accepting the contribution: June 30th, 2014
Early registration for Conference and Workshop: until July 15th, 2016
Late registration for Conference and Workshop: until September 1st, 2016
Submission of full paper: October 28th, 2016

All the essential information is already available on the conference Websit=
e http://www.fdy.tu-darmstadt.de/iti2016/iti2014_1/Home.en.jsp where also L=
aTeX and Word templates for the preparation of the abstracts are made avail=
able.

We are very happy to welcome you in Bertinoro.

We are looking forward to hearing from you soon

Best wishes

________________________________
Martin Oberlack (Technische Universit=E4t Darmstadt)
Joachim Peinke (Universit=E4t Oldenburg / ForWind)
Alessandro Talamelli (Universit=E0 di Bologna)

PS: Please note that September 13-16, 2016 there will be EFMC in Sevilla/Sp=
ain.



--_000_285DB6A636DB57429E9BFC250518D70003980797EX102adstudarms_

[cid:image002.png@01D15391.AC39AF80]

Dear Colleague,

we are pleased to invite you to attend the iTi Conference on Turbulence VII=
 in Bertinoro, Italy, September 7-9, 2016. The iTi (interdisciplinary Turbu=
lence initiative) is a series of conferences organized in order to focus on=
 different aspects of both fundamental and applied turbulence research. The=
refore, both engineers and physicists working in the field of turbulence ar=
e invited to join it.

Topics comprise themes such as: Fundamentals, Modelling, Simulation (DNS an=
d LES), Mathematical Methods, Coherent structure/Vortices, Scaling Laws and=
 Intermittency, Large Re flows experiments, Convection, Polymer and Scalar,=
 Scalar Mixing and Particle, Turbulent Boundary Layers, Atmospheric flows a=
nd MHD.

The seventh conference of the iTi series will again take place in one of th=
e most beautiful conference centers in Europe: the University Centre of Ber=
tinoro. The Centre is located in three large historical and monumental buil=
dings on the top of an ancient town. For further details please check here =
http://www.ceub.it/default.asp?id=3D346#.UqmvjHxQA_Q.

Like in the previous editions the peer reviewed proceedings will be publish=
ed in the volume "Progress in Turbulence VII" by Springer.

The iTi conference will be this year combined with a two-day workshop on Hi=
gh Reynolds number Wall Bounded Turbulent Flows, September 5-6, 2016, organ=
ised by the European consortium EuHIT  (European High-Performance Infrastru=
ctures in Turbulence). The aim of the workshop is to present the new operat=
ive facility "Long Pipe" in CICLoPE (University of Bologna) to both Industr=
ial and Scientific community and to discuss recent developments in measurem=
ent and processing techniques. To attend this workshop an additional regist=
ration is required.

List of iTi invited key-note speakers:
Prof. Alexander Smits, Princeton University
Prof. Bruno Eckhard, University of Marburg
Prof. Paolo Orlandi, Universit=E0 di Roma La Sapienza
Prof. Philipp Schlatter, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm
Prof. Michael Wilczek, Max Planck Institute for Dynamics, G=F6ttingen

Dates and deadlines:
Abstract submission: April 19th, 2016
Response/accepting the contribution: June 30th, 2014
Early registration for Conference and Workshop: until July 15th, 2016
Late registration for Conference and Workshop: until September 1st, 2016
Submission of full paper: October 28th, 2016

All the essential information is already available on the conference Websit=
e http://www.fdy.tu-darmstadt.de/iti2016/iti2014_1/Home.en.jsp where also L=
aTeX and Word templates for the preparation of the abstracts are made avail=
able.

We are very happy to welcome you in Bertinoro.

We are looking forward to hearing from you soon

Best wishes

________________________________
Martin Oberlack (Technische Universit=E4t Darmstadt)
Joachim Peinke (Universit=E4t Oldenburg / ForWind)
Alessandro Talamelli (Universit=E0 di Bologna)

PS: Please note that September 13-16, 2016 there will be EFMC in Sevilla/Sp=
ain.



--_000_285DB6A636DB57429E9BFC250518D70003980797EX102adstudarms_

an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-align:justify;text-autospace:none"><sp=
an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;">The seventh conference of the iTi series will again take place in =
one of the most beautiful conference centers in Europe:
 the University Centre of Bertinoro. The Centre is located in three large h=
istorical and monumental buildings on the top of an ancient town. For furth=
er details please check here
</span><a href=3D"http://www.ceub.it/default.asp?id=3D346#.UqmvjHxQA_Q"><sp=
an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;;color:windowtext">http://www.ceub.it/default.asp?id=3D346#.UqmvjHxQ=
A_Q</span></a><span lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&q=
uot;Helvetica Neue&quot;">.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-align:justify;text-autospace:none"><sp=
an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-align:justify;text-autospace:none"><sp=
an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;">Like in the previous editions the peer reviewed proceedings will b=
e published in the volume &quot;Progress in Turbulence
 VII&quot; by Springer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-align:justify;text-autospace:none"><sp=
an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-align:justify;text-autospace:none"><sp=
an lang=3D"EN-GB" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neu=
e&quot;">The iTi conference will be this year combined with a two-day works=
hop on
<b>High Reynolds number Wall Bounded Turbulent Flows</b>, <b>September 5-6,=
 2016,</b> organised by the
<b>European consortium EuHIT</b>&nbsp; (European High-Performance Infrastru=
ctures in&nbsp;Turbulence). The aim of the workshop is to present the new o=
perative facility &#8220;Long Pipe&#8221; in CICLoPE (University of Bologna=
) to both Industrial and Scientific community and to discuss
 recent developments in measurement and processing techniques. To attend th=
is workshop an additional registration is required.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
